---
import ProjectCard from "./ProjectCard.astro";
---

<ProjectCard
  title="Firefly"
  shortDesc="A terminal music player with over 4k lines of code."
  images={["projects/firefly_v0-7-0.gif", "projects/firefly_mpris.png", "projects/firefly_structure_1.png"]}
>
  <ul class="font-bold text-blue-400 list-disc list-inside">
    <li>First Commit: 2025-07-14 (Now over 600 commits and 30 releases.)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Written in <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://rust-lang.org/"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">Rust</a
    >, featuring <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://guide.elm-lang.org/architecture/"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">The Elm Architecture</a
    > to maintain complexity and ensure scalability.
    <br />
    This project involves multithreading and a web application framework, which exposes me to many new concepts,
    such as
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Atomic Reference Counted Pointer (Arc), Mutex (Lock), and lock poisoning.</li>
      <li>Communicating Sequential Processes (CSP) (<a
        class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
        href="https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/sync/mpsc/index.html"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">MPSC channels</a
      > in Rust).</li>
      <li>Serving files over a TCP listener.</li>
      <li><a
        class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
        href="https://specifications.freedesktop.org/mpris/latest/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer">MPRIS D-Bus Interface Specification.</a
      ></li>
    </ul>

    It primarily supports <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FLAC"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">FLAC</a
    >, MP3, <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Opus_(audio_format)"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">Opus</a
    >, and WAV as of now. Other formats can
    still be used, as the app will automatically convert them to <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FLAC"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">FLAC</a
    > using <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://ffmpeg.org/"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">ffmpeg</a
    >, a multimedia framework.<br />

    This project was developed for my own practical use after my transition to a Linux operating system.
    <br />
  </p>

  <p>
    More detailed information and roadmap in
    <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://github.com/ilialyl/firefly"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Repository</a
    >.
  </p>
  <p>
    Try it on
    <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://github.com/ilialyl/firefly/releases/latest/download/firefly-x86_64-pc-windows-gnu.zip"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">Windows</a
    >
    or
    <a
      class="text-blue-400 font-semibold"
      href="https://github.com/ilialyl/firefly/releases/latest/download/firefly-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu.tar.gz"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer">Linux</a
    >
  </p></ProjectCard
>
